'''Rajiv''' is a common male [[Indian subcontinent|Indian]] name, originating in the [[South Asian]] country of [[India]]. The name means 'lotus flower' in [[Hindi]], and can also be spelled '''Rajeev'''.  In [[Sanskrit]], the word means 'striped'.


